Docker installation
https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-install-and-use-docker-on-ubuntu-16-04

-Open a terminal

-Set up zookeeper container:
$  docker run -d --name zookeeper dockerkafka/zookeeper

-Set up kafka container and link to zookeeper:
$  docker run -d --name kafka --link zookeeper:zookeeper -p 9092:9092 dockerkafka/kafka

-Set up kafka manager and link to zookeeper and kafka
$  docker run -it --rm --link zookeeper:zookeeper --link kafka:kafka -p 9000:9000 -e ZK_HOSTS=zookeeper:2181 dockerkafka/kafka-manager

-Kafka manager will start running straight away, using a certain ip and port.

-Open a browser and go to the ip:port given by Kafka manager (0.0.0.0:9000)

-Create a cluster, and use zookeeper:2181 as hostname

-Optional: create a topic with settings.
A topic will be created automatically

-Write down the broker hostname

-To exit Kafka manager, open a new terminal
$  docker ps
$  docker stop <manager container name>

-Open the /etc/hosts file, and add the broker hostname to the localhost IP

-Use your Kafka library to interface with localhost:9092

//rdKafka
https://github.com/edenhill/librdkafka

